summary: This is an email from the chambers of Judge Alison J. Nathan to counsel in the case US v. Maxwell (20cr330), transmitting the final copy of the court's jury questionnaire for distribution to prospective jurors. The final version incorporates changes from a previous docket entry.

persons.name: Alison J. Nathan
persons.context: The Honorable Judge presiding over the US v. Maxwell case; her chambers sent the email transmitting the final jury questionnaire.

events.title: Jury Questionnaire Distribution
events.description: The final copy of the court's jury questionnaire is to be distributed to prospective jurors beginning the day after this email was sent.

keyFacts: The document is an email dated November 3, 2021, concerning the criminal case US v. Maxwell (docket 20cr330).
The final jury questionnaire for the case was completed and approved for distribution to prospective jurors.
The final version incorporated redline changes from a previous court filing (Dkt. No. 365).
The communication originated from the chambers of the presiding judge, the Honorable Alison J. Nathan.
